commit.message: alpine: add support for auto cairo installing

test: ensure closing surfaces

GitHub: fix GH-82

It's for avoiding StringIO#write calls on Ruby's GC. If surfaces
aren't finished explicitly, they may write something when they are
destroyed. Ruby's GC may destroy them implicitly and it may cause
StringIO#write while GC. It's not acceptable by Ruby.

Reported by Jeremy Bicha. Thanks!!!
